### 4. Purchase Price Allocation: $50.77M NPV Tax Benefit

**REQUIREMENT:** IRC § 1060 mandates both buyer and seller allocate the $425M purchase price among seven asset classes using the **residual method**, with each class absorbing its fair market value before excess flows to the next class.

**PROPOSED ALLOCATION:**

| Class | Asset Category | Allocated Amount | Tax Life (Buyer) | Annual Deduction |
|-------|----------------|------------------|------------------|------------------|
| **Class I** | Cash and cash equivalents | $8.5M | N/A | $0 |
| **Class III** | Accounts receivable | $31.2M | N/A (collected as income) | $0 |
| **Class IV** | Inventory | $2.8M | Expensed as COGS | $2.8M (one-time) |
| **Class V** | Tangible property (real estate, equipment, furniture, vehicles) | $68.5M | 5-27.5 years (MACRS) | $15.1M |
| **Class VI** | Section 197 intangibles (SNF licenses, managed care contracts, non-competes, trade names) | **$73M** | **15 years** | **$4.87M** |
| **Class VII** | Goodwill (residual) | **$241M** | **15 years** | **$16.07M** |
| **TOTAL** | — | **$425M** | — | **$36.03M annually** |

**Key Intangible Asset Valuations (Class VI):**

1. **SNF Licenses (12 facilities):** $50M ($4.17M per facility)
   - **Valuation method:** Per-bed benchmark ($120,300/bed × 1,650 beds = $198.5M theoretical; allocated 11.8% of purchase price = $50M per industry M&A standards)
   - **Rationale:** License is non-transferable by statute, but "going concern value" of licensed facility vs. unlicensed building creates significant intangible value

2. **Managed Care Payor Contracts:** $10M
   - **Valuation method:** Income approach (PV of incremental cash flows from Medicare Advantage/Medicaid MCO contracts paying 5%-8% premium over FFS rates)
   - **Conservative discount:** 41% haircut from $16.9M calculated value (reflects anti-assignment clauses, CHOW rate renegotiation risk)

3. **Non-Compete Agreements (Executives):** $5M
   - **Valuation method:** Differential approach (enterprise value with vs. without non-competes) and direct approach (PV of revenue diversion)
   - **Industry benchmark:** 1.2% of enterprise value (healthcare M&A average: 1.5%-2.5%)

**Tax Benefit Calculation:**

- **Annual deductions:** $36.03M (depreciation + amortization)
- **Federal tax savings @ 21%:** $7.57M annually
- **10-year NPV @ 8% discount rate:** $7.57M × 6.71 (PV annuity factor) = **$50.77M**

**Form 8594 Compliance:**

- Both Silver Oak and Golden Gate Capital must file **Form 8594** (Asset Acquisition Statement) with identical allocations
- **Written allocation agreement** (exhibit to Asset Purchase Agreement) is binding on both parties per IRC § 1060(a)
- **Independent appraisals required:** Real estate (MAI), equipment (healthcare specialist), intangibles (ASA/AVA) - Cost: $250K-$400K

