#### 2. Nevada Commerce Tax (Minimal Impact)

**Nevada is one of seven states with no corporate income tax**, making it the most tax-favorable jurisdiction in this transaction. However, Nevada imposes a **Commerce Tax** on businesses exceeding $4M in Nevada gross revenue.¹³³

##### A. Nevada Commerce Tax Rate

Under **NRS § 363C.510 (Health Care and Social Assistance - NAICS 62)**, the commerce tax rate for skilled nursing facilities is:¹³⁴

| Tax Component | Rate/Threshold | Authority |
|---------------|----------------|-----------|
| **Revenue threshold** | $4,000,000 Nevada gross revenue | NRS § 363C.200 |
| **Taxable base** | Nevada gross revenue **minus $4M** | NRS § 363C.210 |
| **Tax rate (NAICS 62 - Healthcare)** | **0.190%** (19 basis points) | NRS § 363C.510 [VERIFIED via Nevada Legislature] |

**Skilled nursing facilities** (NAICS 623110) fall under NAICS 62 (Health Care and Social Assistance), which has one of the **lowest commerce tax rates** among Nevada business categories (only 8 of 26 categories have lower rates).¹³⁵

##### B. Annual Nevada Commerce Tax Calculation

**Sunset Senior Living Group's Nevada facilities** (4 of 12 facilities = 33.3%) generate estimated annual Nevada gross revenue of:

| Revenue Component | Amount |
|-------------------|--------|
| **Total company revenue (12 facilities)** | $285M annually |
| **Nevada allocation** (4 facilities ÷ 12 facilities) | $285M × 33.3% = **$95M** |
| **Nevada taxable base** | $95M - $4M threshold = **$91M** |
| **Annual Nevada Commerce Tax** | $91M × 0.190% = **$172,900** |

**After-tax cost to Silver Oak:**
- Annual commerce tax: $172,900
- Federal tax deduction: $172,900 × 21% = ($36,309)
- **Net after-tax annual cost: $136,591**

##### C. Asset Purchase vs. Stock Purchase Impact

**CRITICAL: The Nevada Commerce Tax is NOT a one-time transaction tax**—it is an **annual operating tax** based on gross revenue. Therefore, **asset purchase vs. stock purchase structure has NO EFFECT on Nevada Commerce Tax liability**. Silver Oak will pay approximately **$173K annually** regardless of transaction structure.¹³⁶

##### D. Medicare/Medicaid Deductions (Significant Benefit)

Nevada provides a **substantial deduction** for healthcare providers under **NRS § 363C.210(8)**:¹³⁷

> "The total amount of payments received from Medicaid, Medicare, the Children's Health Insurance Program, the Fund for Hospital Care to Indigent Persons, TRICARE, and payments for professional services provided in relation to workers' compensation claims."

**Assuming 78% of Sunset's Nevada revenue derives from Medicare/Medicaid** (industry average for skilled nursing facilities):¹³⁸

| Calculation Step | Amount |
|------------------|--------|
| **Nevada gross revenue** | $95M |
| **Medicare/Medicaid deduction** (78%) | ($74.1M) |
| **Adjusted Nevada taxable base** | $95M - $74.1M - $4M threshold = **$16.9M** |
| **Revised Nevada Commerce Tax** | $16.9M × 0.190% = **$32,110 annually** |

**After-tax cost: $25,367 annually** (net of 21% federal deduction).

**RECOMMENDATION:** Verify Nevada Medicare/Medicaid revenue percentage during due diligence. If **>75% Medicare/Medicaid**, Nevada Commerce Tax exposure drops to **<$35K annually**—effectively de minimis.¹³⁹

