### D. Purchase Price Allocation Methodology (IRC § 1060)

**Purchase price allocation is mandatory for applicable asset acquisitions** under **IRC § 1060**, requiring both buyer and seller to allocate the $425M purchase price among asset classes using the **residual method** prescribed in **Treas. Reg. § 1.338-6**.¹⁵⁸ The allocation directly impacts (1) Silver Oak's annual tax deductions via depreciation/amortization, (2) Golden Gate Capital's taxable gain character (ordinary vs. capital), and (3) state transaction tax exposure on tangible personal property (see Section IV.C).

---

#### 1. IRC § 1060 Residual Method Framework

Under **26 U.S.C. § 1060(a)**, consideration must be allocated in a **waterfall sequence** across seven asset classes, with each class absorbing its fair market value before excess consideration flows to the next class:¹⁵⁹

| Class | Asset Category | Tax Treatment (Buyer) | Tax Treatment (Seller) | Examples |
|-------|----------------|----------------------|------------------------|----------|
| **Class I** | Cash and cash equivalents | No basis adjustment | N/A (cash retained) | Cash on hand, bank deposits |
| **Class II** | Actively traded property | Cost basis; mark-to-market potential | Capital gain/loss | CDs, Treasury securities, publicly traded stock |
| **Class III** | Accounts receivable, mortgages | FMV basis; § 1012 | Ordinary income recapture if collected > basis | Medicare/Medicaid A/R, private-pay A/R |
| **Class IV** | Inventory | Cost basis; COGS deduction on sale | Ordinary income | Medical supplies, PPE, pharmacy inventory |
| **Class V** | All other tangible/intangible property | Depreciable basis (MACRS); varies by asset life | Depreciation recapture (§ 1245) + capital gain | Equipment, furniture, real estate, contracts |
| **Class VI** | Section 197 intangibles (excluding goodwill) | **15-year amortization** | Depreciation recapture + capital gain | SNF licenses, trade names, non-competes, managed care contracts |
| **Class VII** | Goodwill and going concern value | **15-year amortization** | **Capital gain** (20% + 3.8% NIIT) | **Residual allocation** (plug) |

**Critical Rule:** Allocation proceeds **sequentially**—Class VII (goodwill) receives only the **residual** amount after all other classes are satisfied at FMV.¹⁶⁰

