#### 3. SNF License Valuation Methodology (Class VI)

**Skilled nursing facility licenses are among the most valuable intangible assets** in healthcare M&A, representing the legal authorization to operate a Medicare/Medicaid-certified facility. Licenses are **non-transferable by statute** in most states, but the "going concern value" of a licensed facility (vs. an unlicensed building) creates significant intangible value captured in the purchase price.¹⁶²

##### A. Per-Bed Valuation Benchmark

According to the **2017 Senior Care Acquisition Report** (Irving Levin Associates), the average SNF transaction price was **$99,200 per licensed bed**.¹⁶³ Adjusted for inflation (CPI-Medical Care 2017-2024: +21.3%), this equates to **$120,300 per bed in 2024 dollars**.

**Sunset Senior Living Group: 1,650 licensed beds**

| Valuation Method | Calculation | Total License Value |
|------------------|-------------|---------------------|
| **Industry benchmark** | 1,650 beds × $120,300/bed | **$198.5M** |
| **Percentage of purchase price** | $425M × 11.8% (typical SNF license allocation) | **$50.1M** |
| **Per-facility allocation** | $50M ÷ 12 facilities | **$4.17M per facility** |

**For this analysis, we allocate $50M to SNF licenses** ($4.17M per facility), representing **11.8% of total purchase price**—consistent with healthcare M&A benchmarks showing intangible license value at 10%-15% of transaction value.¹⁶⁴

##### B. State Licensure Considerations

| State | Facilities | Licensed Beds | State-Specific Issues |
|-------|-----------|---------------|----------------------|
| **Arizona** | 5 | 688 | Arizona requires change-of-ownership (CHOW) approval by Arizona Department of Health Services (ADHS); bed license transfer requires 30-60 days processing |
| **Nevada** | 4 | 550 | Nevada Bureau of Health Care Quality and Compliance (HCQC) CHOW approval; no CON (Certificate of Need) restrictions |
| **California** | 3 | 412 | California Department of Public Health (CDPH) CHOW approval; strict Medi-Cal enrollment transfer requirements; 60-90 days typical processing |

**CRITICAL:** License transfer failures are **low-probability but high-impact risks**. If any state denies CHOW approval, Silver Oak cannot operate that facility, effectively destroying $35M-$50M in allocated license value. Mitigation: Include **license transfer approval as closing condition** in purchase agreement.¹⁶⁵

